  <lyrics>
	<stanza type="verse" number="1">Once far from God and dead in sin,
  No light my heart could see;
But in God's Word the light I found,
  Now Christ liveth in me.</stanza>
	<stanza type="chorus" number="">Christ liveth in me,
Christ liveth in me;
Oh! what a salvation this,
  That Christ liveth in me.</stanza>
	<stanza type="verse" number="2">As rays of light from yonder sun,
  The flow'rs of earth set free,
So life and light and love come forth
  From Christ living in me.</stanza>
	<stanza type="verse" number="3">As lives the flow'r within the seed,
  As in the cone the tree,
So, praise the Christ of truth and grace,
  His Spirit dwelleth in me.</stanza>
	<stanza type="verse" number="4">With longing all my heart is filled,
  That like Him I may be,
As on the wondrous thought I dwell
  That Christ liveth in me.</stanza>
  </lyrics>
